IAstArrayFunctionParameterIdentifier.description:
The identifier of individual elements of the `Array.map()` function.

`ArrayFunctionParameterIdentifier` is an interface used to identify the
parameters of the callback function in the array transformation function
expression.

For example, if the array transformation function expression used is
{@link IAstArrayMapExpression}, then `ArrayFunctionParameterIdentifier` is
used to identify `value` in `Array.map((value) => ({ ... }))`, and the value
of {@link IAstArrayMapExpression.id} must match
{@link IAstArrayFunctionParameterIdentifier.expression_id}.

Below is an example of using `IAstArrayFunctionParameterIdentifier` and
{@link IAstArrayMapExpression}.

### Code Example
```typescript
const array: number[] = [];
array.map((value, index) => {
  return { id: value + index, age: 20 };
});
```

### Expression
```typescript
{
  type: "ArrayMapExpression",
  id: "some_map_expression_id",
  expression: { type: "Identifier", text: "array" },
  transformer: {
    type: "ObjectLiteralExpression",
    properties: [
      {
        type: "PropertyAssignment",
        name: { type: "Identifier", text: "id" },
        initializer: {
          type: "BinaryExpression",
          left: {
            type: "ArrayFunctionParameterIdentifier",
            expression_id: "some_map_expression_id",
            index: 0,
          },
          operator: "+",
          right: {
            type: "ArrayFunctionIndexIdentifier",
            expression_id: "some_map_expression_id",
          },
        },
      },
      {
        type: "PropertyAssignment",
        name: { type: "Identifier", text: "age" },
        initializer: { type: "NumericLiteral", text: "20" },
      },
    ],
  },
}
```

IAstArrayFunctionIndexIdentifier.description:
Index number identifier in `Array.map()` function.

`ArrayFunctionIndexIdentifier` is an interface used to identify the index
number of the callback function in the array conversion function expression.

For example, if the array conversion function expression used is
{@link IAstArrayMapExpression}, then `ArrayFunctionIndexIdentifier` is used to
identify `index` in `Array.map((_, index) => ({ ... }))` and the value of
{@link IAstArrayMapExpression.id} must match
{@link IAstArrayFunctionIndexIdentifier.expression_id}.

Below is an example of using `IAstArrayFunctionIndexIdentifier` and
{@link IAstArrayMapExpression}.

### Code Example
```typescript
const array: number[] = [...];
array.map((value) => {
  return {
    id: value + index,
    age: 20,
  };
});
```

### Expression
```typescript
{
  type: "ArrayMapExpression",
  id: "some_map_expression_id",
  expression: {
    type: "Identifier",
    text: "array",
  },
  transformer: {
    type: "ObjectLiteralExpression",
    properties: [
      {
        type: "PropertyAssignment",
        name: {
          type: "Identifier",
          text: "id",
        },
        initializer: {
          type: "BinaryExpression",
          left: {
            type: "ArrayFunctionParameterIdentifier",
            expression_id: "some_map_expression_id",
            index: 0,
          },
          operator: "+",
          right: {
            type: "ArrayFunctionIndexIdentifier",
            expression_id: "some_map_expression_id",
          },
        },
      },
      {
        type: "PropertyAssignment",
        name: { type: "Identifier", text: "age" },
        initializer: { type: "NumericLiteral", text: "20" },
      },
    ],
  },
}
```

